1. Core System & Security
apt, apt-utils (package management)
base-files, base-passwd (core system)
bash, dash (shells)
coreutils, util-linux (basic commands)
systemd, systemd-sysv (init system)
udev (device management)
openssh-server (remote access
ufw (firewall)
fail2ban (security, if installed)
cron, logrotate (automation & logs)
rsyslog (logging)

2. Networking
iproute2, net-tools (network utilities)
ifupdown (network config, if used)
dnsutils (dig, nslookup)
openssl (TLS/SSL)
ca-certificates (trusted certificates)

3. Storage & Filesystems
e2fsprogs (ext4 tools)
btrfs-progs (if using Btrfs)
ntfs-3g (if using NTFS)
lvm2 (if using LVM)
gdisk, fdisk (partitioning)

4. Monitoring & Maintenance
htop (process viewer)
strace, lsof (debugging)
ncdu (disk usage analyzer)
smartmontools (disk health)

5. Minimal Web/DB Stack (If Needed)
nginx (or apache2)
mariadb-server (or postgresql)
php8.3-fpm (if using PHP)
certbot (for Letâ€™s Encrypt SSL)

- Development Tools (Remove if Not Needed)
g++, gcc, make, cmake
python3-dev, python3-pip
nodejs, npm, webpack
php*-dev, php*-cli (unless needed)

- Final Minimal Setup
A well-optimized server should only have:
Core OS + Security (systemd, openssh-server, ufw)
Networking (iproute2, dnsutils)
Storage Tools (e2fsprogs, lvm2 if needed)
Monitoring (htop, smartmontools)
Required Services (e.g., nginx, mariadb-server)
